          "description": "Target render width in pixels. When provided, the value is injected into the root <svg> element's width attribute before the browser rasterises the image, overriding any intrinsic width declared in the file. SVGs that carry only a viewBox (no width/height attributes) render as a 0×0 image by default; supplying width and height here fixes that."
